AC  GenProp1043
DE  O145(Ec) antigen biosynthesis
TP  METAPATH
AU  Haft DH
TH  0
CC  The E. coli O145 antigen monomer consists of a linear trimer with the
CC  structure: [->4)aNeu5Ac(2->3)aLFucNAm(1->3)bDGlcNAc(1->], where Neu5Ac
CC  is N-acetyl-neuraminic acid and L-FucNAm is
CC  2-acetamidoylamino-2,6-dideoxy-L-galactose. The LFucNAm transferase
CC  (WbuB) is 98% identical to enzymes in the O151 and O118 antigens where
CC  the same linkage is O145 is found. These are, in turn members of a
CC  clade of such enzymes carrying out the same linkage (with either
CC  LFucNAc or LFucNAm), always at the end of the monomer chain, in
CC  antigens O4, O26, O29, O118, O145, O151, and O172. The WbuW enzyme is
CC  very divergent from other known glycosyltransferases, consistent with
CC  the rare aNeu5Ac(2->3)LFucNAm reaction that it must be carrying out as
CC  inferred by the process of elimination.
--
